un are featured as his relatives. Four episodes were aired in February 1975 on [[CBS]].\n\nDhiegh insisted on having no onscreen billing for his role, despite playing the title character. In an interview to promote the show, he stated, \"To be made the focal point of attention is something that disturbs me greatly. After all, we must remember it is not me, the individual, that is important. That is why I have told CBS I want no credits for the series. The goal is not to make any one person a star, but to create something that is good for all.\"<ref>http://archives.chicagotribune.com/1975/01/26/page/110/article/for-dhiegh-the-villainy-and-virtue-dont-mix/</ref>\n\n==Episodes==\n{{Episode table |total_width= |background=#FFD700 |overall= |title= |airdate= |episodes=\n\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber= 1\n |Title= Khan\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1975|2|7}}\n |ShortSummary= Khan is thrust into the world of professional football to search for a missing star [[quarterback]] accused of killing his girlfriend.|LineColor= FFD700\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber= 2\n |Title= Mask of Deceit\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1975|2|14}}\n |ShortSummary= Khan calls upon his intimate knowledge of the Asian community to trail a mysterious swordsman wearing the mask of a secret Chinese society.|LineColor= FFD700\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber= 3\n |Title= A Game of Terror\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1975|2|21}}\n |ShortSummary= An irate father asks Khan to establish that a young medical intern murdered his daughter, though police believe that the evidence against the suspect is flimsy.|LineColor= FFD700\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber= 4\n |Title= Triad\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1975|2|28}}\n |ShortSummary= The murder of a doctor who was a friend of Khan's leads to a crime syndicate that deals in both gambling and narcotics.|LineColor= FFD700\n}}\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb title|0072528}}\n\n[[Category:1975 American television series debuts]]\n[[Category:1975 American television series endings]]\n[[Category:1970s American crime television series]]\n[[Category:Television series by CBS Television Studios]]\n[[Category:Television shows set in San Francisco]]\n[[Category:American detective television series]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n\n\n{{US-tv-prog-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{For|the 2017 Pakistani television drama serial|Khan (serial)}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name            = Khan!\n| image                = \n| caption              = \n| show_name_2          = \n| genre                = [[Police drama]]\n| creator              = \n| developer            = \n| writer               = [[Michael Fisher (screenwriter)|Michael Fisher]]<br />[[Laurence Heath]]\n| director             = [[Bill Derwin]]<br />[[Ivan Dixon]]\n| creative_director    = \n| presenter            = \n| starring             = [[Khigh Dhiegh]] (uncredited)<br />[[Barbara Baxley]]<br />[[Victor Buono]]<br />[[Joseph Campanella]]<br />[[Richard Carlson (actor)|Richard Carlson]]<br />[[Michael Paul Chan]]\n| judges               = \n| voices               = \n| narrated             = \n| theme_music_composer = \n| opentheme            = \n| endtheme             = \n| composer             = \n| country              = United States\n| language             = English\n| num_seasons          = 1\n| num_episodes         = 4\n| list_episodes        = \n| executive_producer   = \n| producer             = \n| editor               = \n| location             = \n| cinematography       = \n| camera               = \n| runtime              = 60 minutes\n| company              = \n| distributor          = [[CBS Television Distribution]]\n| channel              = [[CBS]]\n| picture_format       = \n| audio_format         = \n| first_run            = \n| first_aired          = {{Start date|1975|2|7}}\n| last_aired           = {{End date|1975|2|28}}\n| preceded_by          = \n| followed_by         